<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-357-478  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 357 478.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>IEEE Transactions on Computers  June 1989 v38 n6 p861(4).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>A note on detecting sneak paths in transistor networks.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Chakravarty, S.; Hunt, H.B., III.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>It is proven that there is no polynomial-time heuristic algorithmthat enables the detection of consistent 'sneak paths' in verysimple transistor networks.andP;  The need to detect such paths ariseswhen transistor networks are minimized.andP;  A proposed polynomialtime heuristic for detecting sneak paths often fails to determinethat a sneak path does not exist.andP;  Proofs that no viablepolynomial-time algorithm for detecting sneak paths are developedand validated.andP;  Details of the underling theorems, lemmas, andproofs are described.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Heuristic MethodsTheoretical ResearchAlgorithmsSystems AnalysisTransistorsNetworksCircuitryValidation.andO;Feature:   illustrationchart.andO;Caption:   1-graphs as representations of Boolean functions. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>